dismissalText.commentary: Rahmanullah Gurbaz b Archer 6 (15b 0x4 0x6 20m) SR: 40

dismissalComment.html: dragged on! No Gurbazball today. Archer's 50th ODI wicket. Very full, swinging in. Gurbaz shapes to drive through the off side but gets a thick inside edge and can only deflect it onto his own stumps, via the pad. 86mph/139kph. Low-key celebration from Archer, just a small fist-pump, but that's a massive early scalp

dismissalText.commentary: Sediqullah Atal lbw b Archer 4 (4b 1x4 0x6 4m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: full and straight, Archer pleads for the lbw... Joel Wilson gives it! Atal will review but only after a long consultation with his partner. Atal planted his front foot and almost managed to get his bat caught behind the pad. Ahsan Raza is satisfied that it's pad first, with the two close together. Pitching in line - albeit only just - and then ball-tracking projects it will smash into middle stump halfway up! Archer has two in the over.

dismissalText.commentary: Adil Rashid c Ibrahim Zadran b Azmatullah Omarzai 5 (7b 0x4 0x6 13m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: Rashid goes big down the ground... and it's caught at long on! AFGHANISTAN HAVE WON BY EIGHT RUNS! Their Champions Trophy dreams remain alive... but England are out of the tournament! A repeat of the 2023 result in the ODI World Cup, but this one will feel so much worse for Englan and Jos Buttler, who is surely on his way out as England captain. But full credit to Afghanistan - first Ibrahim Zadran's special century, and then Azmatullah Omarzai bookending with remarkable figures of 5 for 58 in defense of their score of 325! A truly special night for Afghanistan cricket
